# SonarCloud quality gates (required on every change)

Project: `palepujanakiram_photobooth` in `photobooth/`. See [`docs/sonar-quality.md`](../../docs/sonar-quality.md) (repo root).

When you **add or modify** code under `photobooth/lib/` or `photobooth/test/`, you must satisfy all five gates below before considering the work done.

## 1. No new Maintainability issues

- Do **not** introduce new Sonar code smells (especially `dart:S107` >7 parameters, `dart:S3776` cognitive complexity >15, `dart:S3358` nested ternaries, `dart:S1192` duplicated literals).
- **Fix pattern**: extract helpers (`*_helpers.dart`, `*_widgets.dart`, `*_body.dart`), group parameters into small `*Input` / `*State` / `*Builders` classes, move copy to [`lib/utils/app_strings.dart`](../../photobooth/lib/utils/app_strings.dart).
- Avoid `// NOSONAR` unless documented in the PR; prefer refactoring.

## 2. No new Reliability issues

- No new bugs, null-safety gaps, or fragile async/`BuildContext` use after `await` without `mounted` / `context.mounted` checks.
- Handle API errors with [`utils/exceptions.dart`](../../photobooth/lib/utils/exceptions.dart); report via `ErrorReportingManager` where appropriate.
- Run `dart analyze` from `photobooth/` — zero new analyzer errors.

## 3. Code coverage > 90%

- **SonarCloud (new code)**: keep coverage **above 90%** on changed lines; do not merge if the PR gate fails.
- **In-scope unit-testable layer** (services, utils, models, most ViewModels — see `sonar.coverage.exclusions` / `.qlty/qlty.toml`): add or update tests so scoped files stay at **100%**:

```bash
cd photobooth
flutter test --coverage
dart run tool/verify_coverage_scope.dart
```

- New logic in an in-scope file **requires** matching tests under `photobooth/test/`.
- Pure UI extractions (`*_view.dart`, `*_view_widgets.dart`, `*_body.dart`, `*_helpers.dart` listed in coverage ignores) are excluded from the denominator; do not put business logic there without tests elsewhere.

## 4. No new Security issues

- No new vulnerabilities or unreviewed security hotspots.
- No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or API keys; URLs only via [`lib/utils/app_config.dart`](../../photobooth/lib/utils/app_config.dart).
- Validate/unescape user and network input; use existing secure URL helpers where applicable.

## 5. No new Code Duplication issues

- Keep duplicated lines **≤ 3%** on new code (Sonar gate).
- Reuse shared helpers and [`app_strings.dart`](../../photobooth/lib/utils/app_strings.dart); extract duplicated blocks instead of copy-pasting.
- Do not duplicate API/logging patterns — follow existing `api_service_helpers.dart` / `api_logging/` structure.

## Pre-PR checklist

```bash
cd photobooth
dart analyze
flutter test --coverage
dart run tool/verify_coverage_scope.dart
```

Fix SonarLint (connected mode: `palepujanakiram` / `palepujanakiram_photobooth`). Do not merge if the SonarCloud PR quality gate fails.
